   "source": [
    "Ridge, Lasso y Elasticnet y problemas mal condicionados\n",
    "===\n",
    "\n",
    "* *60 min* | Ultima modificación: Junio 22, 2019"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "En este tutorial se aborda el problema de estimación de problemas mal condicionados en regresión, debido al sobreajuste y memorización de datos"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Problemas mal condicionados"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Preparación"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import matplotlib as mpl\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "%load_ext rpy2.ipython"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import math"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Proceso generador de datos"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "##\n",
    "## Campana de Gauss\n",
    "##\n",
    "def f(x):\n",
    "    x_scaled = [8*z-4 for z in x]\n",
    "    y = [math.exp(-(e**2)) for e in x_scaled]\n",
    "    return np.array(y)\n",
    "\n",
    "##\n",
    "## Note que x está definida en el intervalo [0, 1]\n",
    "##\n",
    "x_real = np.linspace(start=0.0, stop=1.0, num=100)\n",
    "\n",
    "d_real = f(x_real)\n",
    "plt.plot(x_real, d_real, '--', color='gray');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Muestra de datos"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "##\n",
    "## Solo son observables 25 puntos\n",
    "##\n",
    "x_data = np.linspace(start=0.0, stop=1.0, num=25)\n",
    "\n",
    "##\n",
    "## La variable dependiente está contaminada con ruído\n",
    "##\n",
    "np.random.seed(123456)\n",
    "d_data = f(x_data) + np.random.normal(0, 0.1, len(x_data))\n",
    "plt.plot(x_real, d_real, '--', color='gray');\n",
    "plt.plot(x_data, d_data, 'o', color='black');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Modelo polinomial de regresión"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Por facilidad, se usará un polinomio de grado $N$=6 para realizar la regresión:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$y_p = g(x_p) = \\phi_0 + \\sum_{n=1}^N \\phi_n x_p^n$$\n",
    "\n",
    "donde el subíndice $p$ representa cada uno de los puntos de la muestra de datos."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Función de pérdida"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "$$\\text{SSE} = \\sum_{p=1}^P (d_p - y_p)^2 = \\sum_{p=1}^P [d_p - g(x_p)]^2$$ "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Estimación de los coeficientes de la regresión"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def model(N):\n",
    "    w = np.polyfit(x_data, d_data, N)\n",
    "    return np.poly1d(w)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Ajuste para distintos grados del polinomio"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 792x720 with 6 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(11,10))\n",
    "\n",
    "grados = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, n in enumerate(grados):\n",
    "    m = model(n)\n",
    "    y_data = m(x_data)\n",
    "    y_real = m(x_real)\n",
    "\n",
    "    plt.subplot(2, 3, i+1)\n",
    "    plt.plot(x_data, d_data, 'o', color='black');\n",
    "    plt.plot(x_real, d_real, '--', color='black');\n",
    "    plt.plot(x_real, y_real, color='red')\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(n);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Variación en los coeficientes del modelo debido al aumento del grado del polinomio"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def coeffs(N):\n",
    "    return np.flip(np.polyfit(x_data, d_data, N))"
   ]
  },

   "execution_count": 14,

   "source": [
    "df = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'y': d_data,\n",
    "    'x': x_data\n",
    "})\n",
    "df['x2'] = df.x ** 2\n",
    "df['x3'] = df.x ** 3\n",
    "df['x4'] = df.x ** 4\n",
    "df['x5'] = df.x ** 5\n",
    "df['x6'] = df.x ** 6\n",
    "df.head(10)\n",
    "\n",
    "##\n",
    "## Se genera un set de datos para N = 6\n",
    "##"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {

   "source": [
    "##\n",
    "## Se aplica cross-validation para mostrar la variabilidad de los \n",
    "## coeficientes del polinomio debido al cambio del subconjunto de\n",
    "## datos usados para el entrenamiento\n",
    "##\n",
    "\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import KFold\n",
    "from sklearn import linear_model\n",
    "\n",
    "r = pd.DataFrame()\n",
    "\n",
    "kf = KFold(n_splits=10)                        \n",
    "for train, test in kf.split(range(25)):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    regr = linear_model.LinearRegression()\n",
    "    m = regr.fit(df.loc[train, ['x', 'x2', 'x3', 'x4', 'x5', 'x6']].values, df.y[train])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    s = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "        'intercept': m.intercept_,\n",
    "        'x':  [m.coef_[0]],\n",
    "        'x2': [m.coef_[1]],\n",
    "        'x3': [m.coef_[2]],\n",
    "        'x4': [m.coef_[3]],\n",
    "        'x5': [m.coef_[4]],\n",
    "        'x6': [m.coef_[5]]\n",
    "    })\n",
    "    \n",
    "    r = pd.concat([r, s])\n",
    "    \n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "sns.boxplot(data=r)\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=90);    "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Ridge Regression"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "En la regresión ridge, se adiciona una penalización asociada al tamaño de los coeficientes de la regresión:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ \\sum_{i=1}^N (y_i -  w_0 - \\sum_{p=0}^P w_p x_{i,p})^2 + \\alpha * \\sum_{p=0}^P w_p^2 $$\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "donde $\\alpha$ es el peso de la penalización."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Efecto de alpha en los coeficientes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 864x432 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.linear_model import Ridge\n",
    "\n",
    "ridge = Ridge(\n",
    "    alpha=1.0,           #\n",
    "    fit_intercept=True,  #\n",
    "    normalize=False,     #\n",
    "    copy_X=True,         #\n",
    "    max_iter=None,       #\n",
    "    tol=0.001,           #\n",
    "    solver='auto',       # {'auto', 'svd', 'cholesky', 'lsqr', 'sparse_cg', 'sag', 'saga'}\n",
    "    random_state=None)   #\n",
    "\n",
    "coefs = []\n",
    "\n",
    "alphas = np.logspace(-6, 0, 200)\n",
    "\n",
    "y = df.y\n",
    "X = df[['x', 'x2', 'x3', 'x4', 'x5', 'x6']]\n",
    "\n",
    "for a in alphas:\n",
    "    ridge.set_params(alpha=a)\n",
    "    ridge.fit(X, y)\n",
    "    coefs.append(ridge.coef_)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "plt.plot(alphas, coefs)\n",
    "ax = plt.gca()\n",
    "ax.set_xscale('log')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('alpha')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('coeficientes')\n",
    "plt.axis('tight');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Estimación del valor óptimo usando cross-validation"

   "source": [
    "from sklearn.linear_model import RidgeCV\n",
    "\n",
    "ridgeCV = RidgeCV(\n",
    "    alphas = 10 ** np.linspace(-10, -3, 200),\n",
    "    cv = None,\n",
    "    store_cv_values = True\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",

   "source": [
    "## LASSO"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "En este modelo, el término de penalización es el valor absoluto de los coeficientes del modelo de regresión. Mientras que en la regresión ridge, los coeficientes $w_i$ tienden a ser pequeños, LASSO tiende a llevarlos a cero:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ \\sum_{i=1}^N (y_i -  w_0 - \\sum_{p=0}^P w_p x_{i,p})^2 + \\alpha * \\sum_{p=0}^P ||w_p|| $$\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Efecto de alpha sobre los coeficientes del modelo"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 67,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {

     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.linear_model import Lasso\n",
    "\n",
    "## https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/generated/sklearn.linear_model.Lasso.html\n",
    "\n",
    "lasso = Lasso(\n",
    "    alpha=1.0,            #\n",
    "    fit_intercept=True,   #\n",
    "    normalize=False,      #\n",
    "    precompute=True,    #\n",
    "    copy_X=True,          # \n",
    "    max_iter=100000,      #\n",
    "    tol=0.000001,         #\n",
    "    warm_start=True,      #\n",
    "    positive=False,       #\n",
    "    random_state=12345,   #\n",
    "    selection='random')   #\n",
    "    \n",
    "coefs = []\n",
    "\n",
    "alphas = np.logspace(-3, -1, 200)\n",
    "\n",
    "y = df.y\n",
    "X = df[['x', 'x2', 'x3', 'x4', 'x5', 'x6']]\n",
    "\n",
    "for a in alphas:\n",
    "    lasso.set_params(alpha=a)\n",
    "    lasso.fit(X, y)\n",
    "    coefs.append(lasso.coef_)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "plt.plot(alphas, coefs)\n",
    "ax = plt.gca()\n",
    "ax.set_xscale('log')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('alpha')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('coeficientes')\n",
    "plt.axis('tight');"
   ]
  },

    "## Elastic Net"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Este modelo combina las penalizaciones de ridge y LASSO en un solo modelo:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ \\sum_{i=1}^N (y_i - w_0 - w_1 x_i)^2 + \\alpha \\rho * (|w_0| + |w_1|) + \\frac{\\alpha (1 - \\rho)}{2}(w_0^2 + w_1^2)$$\n"
   ]
